stimulus:
In this task, you will see a set of three symbols. These symbols can be the number 1, 2, 3, or the letter X. Two of the symbols will be the same, and one will be different.

Your task is to press the number on your keyboard corresponding to the symbol which is different from the other two.

During some trials, the position of the symbol which is different will match the position of the button you must press:

1 X X

(Here, you would press 1.)

During other trials, the position of the symbol which is different will not match the position of the button you must press:

2 3 3

(Here, you would press 2.)

Each trial will be followed by fixation on a black cross.

The following page is a test to check your understanding of the instructions.

Press any key to continue.
